tip.text: Cheesecake is the main star here. Forget about the mango sundae which tasted funny with its sour plum, choc, mango and chilli flakes combination. Happy hour of buy 1for1 is great too.

I came here with longing crave for their pork but end up really disappointed. Pork belly were fatty and pork rib were dry and gamy. Porky fries not crunchy with a soft centre. Price point is steep too

venue.name: Sis & Co Deli Coffee Restaurant Bar

formattedAddress: Empire Damansara (Lot 103, First Floor), Jalan PJU 8/8
location.address: Empire Damansara (Lot 103, First Floor), Jalan PJU 8/8

tip.text: Pork toast, chicken chop, congee and house bowl are all great but the place can get abit stuffy with it's open kitchen. You will come out smelling after having dinner here
They have this koyaku course dinner at rm52 which is really filling and ingredients are all fresh. Try the spider maki too!
Loving the entrance of the restaurant and breakfast buffet is rm40. Wantan rose is sooo cutee and crunchy too!
Pulut tai tai is quite exquisite with hints of kaya taste. Will be back to try other unique flavours! Yumz!!
Seriously Burnt wedges; dry and super hard eating it while it was hot. Coffee is decent tho
Rissotto and genkishan is quite reasonable and tasty. Just be careful not to seat next to the alley on the left coz there's mouse the size of a kitten.
Mushroom risotto is fantastic with a sprinkle of the mushroom powder. Service is fantastic with a brief explanation of each dishes. Try the degustation menu it changes everyday
Everything is delicious and yumz!try the half half soy and sweet and spicy chicken and chick buldak. Price is on a high side tho

location.address: 66, First Floor, Jalan 27/70a, Desa Sri Hartamas, Kuala Lumpur
formattedAddress: 66, First Floor, Jalan 27/70a, Desa Sri Hartamas, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Everything is great here! Try the spider maki and Their seasonal Sakura items like sochu, soba and desserts. Environment is also serene and beautiful too.
Beautiful cafe with a little nook to purchase flowers and nick nacks. Limited and mediocre food choices tho come for the cakes! Cute and delectable. Yumz!
Everything is great here! Have the snow squid toppoki, soya chicken wings, watermelon soju and yangpa bomb! Will definitely come back to try others! 😛😛
A breakfast joint at an unlikely place in pudu. Decent sandwiches with reasonable price tho the place is quite cramp and small.

formattedAddress: Pavilion KL, 168 Jalan Bukit Bintang, (Level 1, Lot No. 1.108.00)

tip.text: Great hangout place with a view of the cbd. Try the prawn tapas and pavlova cocktail
Great selections of fish to choose from. Had the gummy shark for fish and chip and it's totally drool worthy. Have the charred corn too. It's sooo good
Acres of plantation with a spectacular view. Try the slider and kingfish tho the pricing is on the steep side
One of the best Thai fusion I have in Australia. Try the roasted pork belly, super yumzzz!
Ambience and food is comfortable and palatable. Recommend the egg, ulam rice and the mushroom egg.
The better hotpot available in Malaysia. Tho I still think hai di lau triumph in terms of the broth flavour.

contact.facebookName: Chunciou Hot Pot Malaysia 马来西亚春秋战锅

venue.name: Chun-Ciou Hot Pot 春秋战锅 (Chun-Ciou hot pot)

tip.text: Decent food with very comfortable ambience. The only fall back is the steep pricing.
They have a full fledged choice of brunch here tho queue can be long and pricing can be steep
The squid toppoki cheese is just to die for.. you savour every piece of the cheese spicy flavour sauce slowly. The dakgalbi however was jelak towards the end. Couldn't finish our meal at all

venue.name: Omaya 春州炒鸡 · 部队锅 · 铜盘烤肉

tip.text: Chocoreto pancake is awesome with chunks of banana bits. The ying&yang waffles on the other hand is just normal.
Pancakes and big breakkie was awesome tho coffee wasn't that great. Loving the coffee bar where you could see the brewing going on.

formattedAddress: A-G-1, New Podium, Plaza Vads, 1 Jalan Tun Mohd Faud
location.address: A-G-1, New Podium, Plaza Vads, 1 Jalan Tun Mohd Faud

tip.text: Ham&Cheese taiyaki is so cheesy and sinful. Melon bingsu is also super yumz!
Sirloin 200g is just perfectly cooked medium rare. Seafood is awesome too. Definitely a place for steak lover
Shiok makiiiiii is so freaking gooddd
Snow squid toppoki and soju watermelon slushie! A must order when coming over
Dim sum and the duck is famous here. Great place for brunch

venue.name: Imperial Treasure Super Peking Duck Restaurant

tip.text: Service and environment is cheerful and friendly. Tried the beef wellington and wasn't fantastic. Fish&chip, salmon tartare and scallop is simply delishz!! Come over for some Halloween specials too.

formattedAddress: L1-81 The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands (2 Bayfront Avenue)
location.address: L1-81 The Shoppes at Marina Bay Sands

tip.text: Try the Halloween theme food here. Everything from the poison apple to digging grave is great. Have the waffles, mushroom soup, soft shell crab pasta and signature  coffee..
Breakfast pudding. Enuff said
Everything from the environment to the food was great. Service was impeccable and friendly. Definitely a must go place for Japanese lover
Environment and coffee is decent. A better alternative in TTDI if you wanna avoid the hazard of parking
Pancake is fluffy and super moist. We can't help but got seconds. Meatloaf was good tho the waffles is just mediocre.
Place is super chic and cute! Food is decent and they have cold brew and beer too. What more could you ask for.
Sashimi and mentai rice is awesome. Great place to go if you like raw food and fish

location.address: Plaza Damas 3 (Lot B-0-7), Jalan Sri Hartamas 1
formattedAddress: Plaza Damas 3 (Lot B-0-7), Jalan Sri Hartamas 1

tip.text: Alcoholic ice cream. Enuff said
Greentea bingsu is super nice! The environment and service was superb too! Only concern was the kpop music blaring so loud in the background
The salmon salad ball is so good that we finished the whole thing within 5mins. Everything else was great too! Worth the money spent!
More variety than dip&dip and presentation and environment is superb. Give the sizzling brownie a try!
Food was great but kinda pricey. Choco dip and buffalo wings is yumz. Variety of tea is a must order..
Humongous pork knuckle, great piggy fries and nacho that is super yummy! Reasonable priced with lively environment. Definitely coming back!
Bread is excellent here. Everything from croissant and garlic bread is good. Coffee is decent too!
Great savoury and sweet pancakes to choose from. Don't bother coming for the coffee tho. Too mild

contact.facebookName: Beary Potter Studio Cafe       熊の 陶工房

venue.name: Beary Potter Studio Café (陶工房べア)

tip.text: Soufflé, choc lava and earl grey milk tea is their specialty here. Love their white minimalist tho not a place to seek for coffee
8 flavour porks is their specialty here. Do try the cheese stir fried rice too. Ventilation is bad so be prepared coming out all sweaty and smelly
Sharing platter, beef pizza and lamb moussaka is great for sharing and taste good. Environment is also decent and you get to enjoy the waterfall outside especially its night view

venue.name: Svago Cucina e Musica & Limoncello Italian Bistro & Bar

tip.text: Good porky places around setiawalk puchong around. Try the porky pasta and its signature pork ribs.. Love it to bits
Medium well spare ribs, escargot, potato skin and garlic bread is really finger licking good. Come here just for the steak! Yumz
Salted egg spaghetti is good tho feel jelak after a few mouth. Salted egg cronut is totally an overhype, cold and super sweet.

location.neighborhood: Taman Tun Doktor Ismail, Kuala Lumpur, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Environment is rara and stylish while food and dessert is really good.. Recommended dish is Spring chick, pavlova, hamachi and the watermelon starter. Book before you go coz it's always full
Great food, decent coffee and friendly staff.. Owner looks cute too! Definitely a to-go place other than the good batch.
Philly steak and it's variety of smoothie is really good. Churros is just mediocre tho..

formattedAddress: 60000 Taman Tun Dr. Ismail, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Balik kampong and big breakfast is really quite good tho the queue can be long and service can get frizzle.
Everything is delectable here especially the white maguro and salmon belly. Set lunch is also worth the price. Will definitely come back
Loving the vibe and environment here. Food is delectable and coffee is awesome! Will come back again
Cheese is the main attraction here. You could use anything from squid to kimchi to dip it. Price is reasonable here.
Dense flavour for a softserve. Eclipse is nice with the kaitan zhai served together..
No doubt the hype is legit but you feel uncomfortable dining there as staff shouted for orders, disorganized staff taking order of the croissants and staff yelling our names to take our bread..
So far the best soft serve I have ever try.. The hojicha is soooo good. Definitely coming back again.
Warm and cosy ambience with cute owl deco concept. Waffles is the only thing worth ordering here tho not a good coffee place. Coffee too mild for my taste bud

formattedAddress: Block 5 (Unit 12-1), Jalan Jalil Jaya 6 (Jalil Link, Jalan Jalil Jaya 6,)

tip.text: Pork belly is one of the better ones in PJ. Pork pepperoni was just mediocre
Service is great and friendly. Worth to try the gula melaka latte and it's porky dishes.
Insta-worthy images but that's just all that is to it. Yogurt is sourish and the fish cake texture is abit soft at the bottom part.
Beef hamburg curry katsu is worth a try. Go for level 8 for the right spicy kick. Coffee and service is commendable too.
Price is a little steep but beats dal.komm and cafe benne on the smoothness of the shave ice. So far the best bingsu I had try.
The creation and idea of custom made ice cream is creative and super instra- worthy. Only fall back is their super expensive price tag.
The presentation look super nice but price point is on a steep side
Loving the European and the ice cube hazelnut coffee. Everything taste great. Go during 4pm where the crowd shimmer down a little
Beef bacon and cold drip is a real nice kick to an early breakfast. Had the tea meets coffee but wasn't really spectacular. Love it here.
Food presentation and service is on point. Try their spicy maguro, creative cocktails and tempura. Got a complementary yuzu ice cream after finishing meal. Will definitely come back again!

formattedAddress: Ground Floor Atria Shopping Gallery (Jalan SS22)

tip.text: Hipster place with reasonable price. Try the shakerato, ice vanilla latte, banana & choc pancake and chili fries. The waiter was nice when we asked for extra choc dip for the pancake. FOC
Roast pork was really good. Juicy meat with crispy crackling. Ordered the platter and truffle fries. Go early for the happy hour! Super worthwhile.

formattedAddress: Unit G-2, The Sphere (Jalan Kerinchi, Bangsar South)

tip.text: Loving the environment and waffles here. Staff were attentive and coffee and desserts were executed well
Coffee is really really good. Ordered the nutella, latte and cappuccino and everything tastes good. Only regret was the cakes, nice to see but wasn't good on palate. Skip it

formattedAddress: 2-1 jalan PJU 5/4, Dataran Sunway, Kota Damansara
location.address: 2-1 jalan PJU 5/4, Dataran Sunway, Kota Damansara

tip.text: Best baked salted prawns and lala. Fried sotong is really good too! Definitely coming back.

venue.name: Sea Pearl Lagoon Cafe (海珠嶼海鮮)

tip.text: Love love love the Mango cup! Enough said.
The waffles is really bad... Like hard as stone bad. And the coffee Taufufa also tasted weird. The only good side is the s'mores.
The gyudon with spring onion and egg is super yummylicious tho the vege that came along was not edible at all. Choose the set meal with the karaage instead which is more value for money
They are famous for it's cheese cake with really cute packaging. A must go place in Ginza.

formattedAddress: 銀座8-8-3 (東京銀座資生堂ビル)

venue.name: Shiseido Parlour (資生堂パーラー 銀座本店)

tip.text: Millie crepe is their specialty here. Go for their 3 in 1, durian crepe and rum and raisin flavour. Super yumzz!

formattedAddress: No. 22 A-1, Jalan PJU 5/21, Pusat Perdagangan Kota Damansara, Kota Damansara PJU 5, , (Kota Damansara)
location.address: No. 22 A-1, Jalan PJU 5/21, Pusat Perdagangan Kota Damansara, Kota Damansara PJU 5, ,

venue.name: Winter Lover Bakery House 冬の恋人ベーカリー

tip.text: The almond croissant is just heavenly. Pair it with a cuppa cappuccino and it taste just right for a sunny weekend morning.
Everything tasted real good here. From the hot chocolate to the roasted beef ciabiatta to it's jam and cream scones. Definitely a great place to start your weekend morning!
Food was great overall. Love the escargot, chicken Madison and choc lava cake. Definitely worth a second visit...

formattedAddress: D6-7-G, Blk 7, Pusat Perdagangan Dana 1 (Jalan PJU 1A/46, PJU1A)
D6-7-G, Blk 7, Pusat Perdagangan Dana 1 (Jalan PJU 1A/46, PJU1A)
D6-7-G, Blk 7, Pusat Perdagangan Dana 1 (Jalan PJU 1A/46, PJU1A)

D6-7-G, Blk 7, Pusat Perdagangan Dana 1 (Jalan PJU 1A/46, PJU1A)

tip.text: Try to park outside of Avenue 8 near the shop lots as parking can cost ard rm2 an hour. Also, try the urban legend and the mash from the pork chop! Porktantastic!
Love the caramelised roast pork and the BBQ pork rib. Yummy yumzzz..
Bread & butter pudding was not hot and texture was too starchy. Overall a place I would not be revisiting again. Only upside was the choc Oreo milkshake that is so lip smacking good.
Pork ribs is huge so do opt to share among friends and family. Do try their porky ice cream. It's so finger licking good...
Must haves: traffic and mushroom soup, try avoid the country roasted chicken as it's kinda dry..
Love love love the penne Alfredo and their choc brownie with ice cream. The place can be quite pack during peak hours..

formattedAddress: Danau Business Center, 11-0-12, Jalan 3/109F (Taman Danau Desa)
Danau Business Center, 11-0-12, Jalan 3/109F (Taman Danau Desa)
Danau Business Center, 11-0-12, Jalan 3/109F (Taman Danau Desa)

tip.text: Pair the lamberghini burger with their homemade chilli sauce and end your superb meal with red velvet. Heavenlicious!!
Cute coffee art they did that totally lighten up my morning. Breakfast is totally yumzz as well. Avoid coming ard 10-11ish as the crowd is crazy and things gets a little frizzle
The banana bread pudding is super yummz but do not ever have the aglio olio clam it taste bland and dry. Totally the worst I ever taste.

formattedAddress: 16, Lorong Rahim Kajai 14, Taman Tun Dr Ismail (Taman Tun Dr Ismail)
location.address: 16, Lorong Rahim Kajai 14, Taman Tun Dr Ismail

tip.text: The butter croissant is just oh soo good~! I just had to come back for that!
The set lunch: ayam percik is super awesome and the ambience and food presentation is lovely as well. Come here for some authentic Malay food.

items.firstName: Kelvin Wong @ 王凱民 @ Mr. K

tip.text: Nice ambience with really cute waiter. Sadly, the red velvet is not up to my expectation. If u really like red velvet, better to go Plan B instead.
Original crepe all the way! A must go place when visiting malacca.
Come here just for the fresh sashimi and free green tea ice cream. Droolzzz
A place with local and international brand. Check out their spice bar with all their varieties too. Love this
Pizza is their speciality here. Newly open, the salmon and egg is really delicious and great for sharing.

venue.name: Comida - The Way We Like It

tip.text: Love the Christmas deco and the design here. It is divided into few blocks so beginners will be abit confused when u wanna find something to eat here...
The ambience is so inviting and lovely...

formattedAddress: Kuala Lumpur, Federal Territory of Kuala Lum

tip.text: Cappuccino mushroom soup is just so heavenly...
Garlic rice in hot stone is just soooo good!
Hoegarden is really cheap during happy hours till 10pm.
Things is abit pricy with the portion they are selling! Tasted better tofu desserts but their earl grey milk tea is totally irresistable!
Cute deco+cute cakes+coffee art= girls heaven! Tried the mocha! It super delishZz but green tea layer cake is quite normal and lacks the flavour in it

location.address: 32-1, The Strand, Jalan PJU 5/20D, Kota Damansara
formattedAddress: 32-1, The Strand, Jalan PJU 5/20D, Kota Damansara

tip.text: Rosemary chicken is cooked tender on the inside crispy on the outside. The cappriciossa pizza is loveable too and end your meal with a 5 layer ice cream cake
Not sure about the bad press here but the banana pizza is actually quite decent, same goes for my unagi pasta that was served steaming hot
Love the deco, love the sticky bones and everything there. I just didn't like the steep price there! 2 girls for Rm160++ is just..... too much!!
Brownies with vanilla ice cream tastes great. Staffs are attentive as well
Dishes are super creative with their Thai and Japanese fusion exp their spaghetti meitaiko and black fried rice
Squid ink pasta is awesome but warning: don't have on your first date it will just ruin your first impression
Desserts here is just so so tempting! Do leave some space for that while u stuff yourself with those oversized oysters!
The tiramisu is just OH SOOO HEAVENLY~! I will come back just for that!~

formattedAddress: lot g6 & g7 ground floor (3 Lebuh Bandar Utama)

tip.text: Bought choc cake for my sis's bday and it taste great!! But after a few days the cake got really dry! Should let customers know that!
